Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve and very thinly slice the @red onion{1} and pop
half of it into a small #bowl{}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop them
into another small bowl. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve
lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can}
in a #sieve{}. Halve the @lime{1/2}.

Add half the lime juice to the bowl with the sliced red onion with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @sugar{pinch}. Stir well and set aside. Cut the remaining lime
into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is
hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Once browned, add the remaining
onion and cook, stirring, until softened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add three
quarters of the @chipotle paste{20%g} and all the @tomato puree{30%g} and cook,
stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{100%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1%tsp}, stir to dissolve the
stock powder. Stir in the black beans and use a #masher{} to gently crush them.
Season with salt and @pepper{} and bring to a simmer. Cook until thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the remaining chipotle paste into the bowl with the halved
tomatoes. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, season with salt and pepper and
mix well. Once the pork is nearly ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a
#baking tray{} and bake on the top shelf of your oven until warmed through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Reheat the pork mixture until piping hot. > Add a splash more water if dry! Taste
and season with salt and pepper if you like. Divide the tacos between plates and
spoon over the pork and black bean mixture. Top with the sliced lettuce then
spoon over the chipotle tomatoes and finish with the pickled red onion. Serve
with the lime wedges alongside.

> Enjoy!